The Delray Beach Open is an ATP World Tour 250 series men's professional tennis tournament held each year in Delray Beach, Florida, and played on hard courts. The event was held in Coral Springs from 1993â€“1998; in 1999, it was relocated to the Delray Beach Tennis Center. American Todd Martin won the tournament's first singles event in 1993.
The tournament was previously named the Delray Beach International Tennis Championships (ITC) before being changed to its current name in 2014.


